==English==
===Etymology===
From [[eminent]] + [[-ly]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'ɛmɪnəntli/}}

===Adverb===
{{en-ad|eminently}}
# in an [[eminent]] or [[prominent]] manner
# to a great degree; [[notably]], [[highly]]
#: ''Everyone supported the nominee because she was '''eminently''' qualified.''

